headline: Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q4 CY2025 But Stock Drops 33.4%
summary: Healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 8.3% year on year to $11.38 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $44.5 billion at the midpoint came in 4.9% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP loss of $2.75 per share was significantly below analysts’ consensus estimates.
